1
00:00:07,661 --> 00:00:09,663
ABE: You're walking way too fast.

2
00:00:09,747 --> 00:00:10,914
What room did she say?

3
00:00:10,998 --> 00:00:12,332
Twelve. Room 12.

4
00:00:12,416 --> 00:00:13,750
I think she said ten.

5
00:00:13,834 --> 00:00:15,794
-I heard eight.
-She said 12.

6
00:00:15,878 --> 00:00:18,088
I'll go back and check.
Should I go back and check?

7
00:00:18,172 --> 00:00:19,798
Yes. Go back and check.

8
00:00:19,882 --> 00:00:21,216
ABE: Are you being sarcastic?

9
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,676
MIDGE: The cab driver was an idiot.

10
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:24,260
ROSE: We're so sorry, Shirley.

11
00:00:25,095 --> 00:00:26,638
Oy, my God.

12
00:00:26,722 --> 00:00:28,223
It's bad, isn't it, Abe?

13
00:00:28,307 --> 00:00:30,350
Papa? You want to go get people coffee?

14
00:00:30,434 --> 00:00:32,185
-Who wants coffee?
-OTHERS: Mm-mm.

15
00:00:32,269 --> 00:00:34,813
-Everyone wants coffee.
-Guess I'll get coffee.

16
00:00:34,897 --> 00:00:36,690
-Oh.
-What are they saying?

17
00:00:36,774 --> 00:00:38,941
-They say he's going to die.
-They didn't say that.

18
00:00:39,025 --> 00:00:40,818
Well, they said he's
probably going to die.

19
00:00:40,902 --> 00:00:42,820
Ma, they're still doing tests.

20
00:00:42,904 --> 00:00:44,363
A lot of tests but no word yet.

21
00:00:44,447 --> 00:00:46,490
"No word" means he's
definitely going to die.

22
00:00:46,574 --> 00:00:47,950
You don't know that, Shirley.

23
00:00:48,034 --> 00:00:49,827
-You know something that I don't?
-No.

24
00:00:49,911 --> 00:00:51,787
That gypsy fortune teller
speak to somebody upstairs

25
00:00:51,871 --> 00:00:52,955
and tell you the future?

26
00:00:53,039 --> 00:00:54,081
-Ma.
-Because I was sitting

27
00:00:54,165 --> 00:00:55,374
right here when the doctor said

28
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:58,711
he absolutely,
positively is going to die.

29
00:00:58,795 --> 00:01:00,254
Miriam!

30
00:01:00,338 --> 00:01:01,672
I didn't bring my wallet.

31
00:01:01,756 --> 00:01:03,382
That's okay. No one wants coffee.

32
00:01:03,466 --> 00:01:05,134
Then why did you send me to get coffee?

33
00:01:05,218 --> 00:01:07,720
Just stay with Shirley and don't speak.

34
00:01:07,804 --> 00:01:10,139
But… But where are you going?

35
00:01:10,223 --> 00:01:11,390
We'll be right back.

36
00:01:11,474 --> 00:01:12,975
Could you bring me a coffee?

37
00:01:13,059 --> 00:01:15,520
Mm-hmm. Are you okay?

38
00:01:15,645 --> 00:01:17,521
I killed him. I killed my father.

39
00:01:17,605 --> 00:01:18,981
-Joel, no.
-Yes.

40
00:01:19,065 --> 00:01:20,691
Yes, I'm like that guy, uh…

41
00:01:20,775 --> 00:01:22,109
-Who was it?
-Who was who?

42
00:01:22,193 --> 00:01:23,694
The guy in the Bible
that killed his father.

43
00:01:23,778 --> 00:01:25,112
I don't know. Uh, Abraham?

44
00:01:25,196 --> 00:01:27,281
No.
He was the one who almost killed his son.

45
00:01:27,365 --> 00:01:29,241
-Absalom?
-No. It didn't start with an "A."

46
00:01:29,325 --> 00:01:30,826
Uh, Oedipus?

47
00:01:30,910 --> 00:01:32,578
-That's not the Bible.
-But he killed his father.

48
00:01:32,662 --> 00:01:33,746
And married his mother.

49
00:01:33,830 --> 00:01:35,456
Well, other than that, I'm that guy.

50
00:01:35,540 --> 00:01:39,585
-Joel… What happened?
-[SIGHS]

51
00:01:39,669 --> 00:01:42,171
He, uh, he came to the club.
He had the costumes with him.

52
00:01:42,255 --> 00:01:44,423
-Uh, a pineapple, a carrot. Very cute.
-I know.

53
00:01:44,507 --> 00:01:46,425
Oh, there was an option
of them both being grapes.

54
00:01:46,509 --> 00:01:47,885
If you wanted to keep
Esther from running off,

55
00:01:47,969 --> 00:01:49,178
-you'd tie 'em together like a bunch of…
-Uh-huh.

56
00:01:49,262 --> 00:01:50,304
-Circle back around, honey.
-Right.

57
00:01:50,388 --> 00:01:52,431
Uh, so I thought, he's here, he's happy.

58
00:01:52,515 --> 00:01:54,433
Good time to tell him about Mei.

59
00:01:54,517 --> 00:01:56,142
-What did you say?
-I was nervous,

60
00:01:56,226 --> 00:01:58,603
so I… I just blurted shit
out, and I think I kind of

61
00:01:58,687 --> 00:02:00,313
mushed "Chinese" and "pregnant" together.

62
00:02:00,397 --> 00:02:02,315
I should've let one sink in,
then hit him with the other.

63
00:02:02,399 --> 00:02:03,733
I don't think it was you.

64
00:02:03,817 --> 00:02:06,027
Really. I think it was me.

65
00:02:06,111 --> 00:02:07,612
-What?
-I did it. I killed Moishe.

66
00:02:07,696 --> 00:02:08,863
-You did not kill Moishe.
-Our last conversation,

67
00:02:08,947 --> 00:02:10,490
I told him I couldn't pay him his money,

68
00:02:10,574 --> 00:02:12,325
and he literally told me he
was having a heart attack.

69
00:02:12,409 --> 00:02:13,785
-When was this?
-Two weeks ago.

70
00:02:13,869 --> 00:02:15,328
Pretty slow heart attack.

71
00:02:15,412 --> 00:02:17,163
But maybe I laid the track for
him to have the heart attack.

72
00:02:17,247 --> 00:02:19,457
Got him started, and then you
came in and finished him off.

73
00:02:19,541 --> 00:02:21,209
-This is very comforting.
-You didn't kill your father.

74
00:02:21,293 --> 00:02:22,919
-Well, neither did you.
-DOCTOR: Room 12. Moishe Maisel.

75
00:02:23,003 --> 00:02:24,462
The wife's a hysterical.

76
00:02:24,546 --> 00:02:26,506
-[DOCTOR SIGHS]
-I… I should get back in there

77
00:02:26,590 --> 00:02:27,882
to listen to them tell us nothing.

78
00:02:27,966 --> 00:02:29,217
Because otherwise, it's a long time

79
00:02:29,301 --> 00:02:30,593
before they come back to tell us nothing.

80
00:02:30,677 --> 00:02:32,762
Twelve. I think it's room 12.
Joel, Midge, how is he?

81
00:02:32,846 --> 00:02:34,472
We don't know. He's unconscious.

82
00:02:34,556 --> 00:02:35,473
ARCHIE: Unconscious?

83
00:02:35,557 --> 00:02:37,558
[GROANS] Jesus. I'm so sorry.

84
00:02:37,642 --> 00:02:40,645
-Thanks, pal.
-No, I mean…

85
00:02:40,729 --> 00:02:42,355
-I killed your father, Joel.
-What?

86
00:02:42,439 --> 00:02:44,065
ARCHIE: I lost the money.

87
00:02:44,190 --> 00:02:46,192
If that money hadn't have
gotten ripped out of my hands…

88
00:02:46,276 --> 00:02:47,819
-Archie.
-That's when all the trouble started.

89
00:02:47,903 --> 00:02:49,654
I had nothing to do with
this, so I'll just be the person

90
00:02:49,738 --> 00:02:51,239
-who pats people's arms.
-Calm down, Arch.

91
00:02:51,323 --> 00:02:52,532
Really. It's nice you're here.

92
00:02:52,616 --> 00:02:53,908
Should I go tell your
mother it was my fault?

93
00:02:53,992 --> 00:02:55,827
-I'll do it later.
-MEI: This way to room 12?

94
00:02:55,911 --> 00:02:57,620
Finally.
I left you a message over an hour ago.

95
00:02:57,704 --> 00:02:59,247
-Where have you been?
-Yankee Stadium.

96
00:02:59,331 --> 00:02:59,472
Why?

97
00:02:59,556 --> 00:03:01,082
Because the message you left Li Wei said,

98
00:03:01,166 --> 00:03:02,542
"Go to Yankee Stadium."

99
00:03:02,626 --> 00:03:03,918
I've got to get a better
fucking dictionary.

100
00:03:04,002 --> 00:03:06,171
-How is he?
-[SIGHS]

101
00:03:07,422 --> 00:03:09,966
-JOEL: I don't know.
-MEI: He'll be okay.

102
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:12,218
ABE: Wait, what was that?
What just happened?

103
00:03:12,302 --> 00:03:14,219
Yeah, I'm getting a lot of action today.

104
00:03:14,303 --> 00:03:16,221
Doctor! Get the doctor.

105
00:03:16,305 --> 00:03:17,556
-Why? What happened?
-ROSE: Abe!

106
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:19,808
Get back here. Nothing's changed.

107
00:03:19,892 --> 00:03:21,977
I distinctly heard a death rattle.

108
00:03:22,061 --> 00:03:24,396
You just dropped your keys.

109
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:26,899
Come on, Papa. I'll hold your keys.

110
00:03:30,444 --> 00:03:32,494
[PERRY COMO: "HERE COMES HEAVEN AGAIN"]

111
00:03:34,448 --> 00:03:36,950
ROSE: <i>Okay, Abe, Zelda
and I are heading to the house</i>

112
00:03:37,034 --> 00:03:39,536
<i>to get Shirley's things.</i>

113
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:42,122
Try to get some rest, Shirley.

114
00:03:42,206 --> 00:03:44,124
Mm.

115
00:03:45,668 --> 00:03:46,960
[SIGHS]

116
00:03:47,044 --> 00:03:53,717
[ON TV] <i>♪ Get that angel face ♪</i>

117
00:03:55,344 --> 00:03:56,595
[SNIFFLES]

118
00:03:56,679 --> 00:04:03,018
<i>♪ You don't need a halo or wings… ♪</i>

119
00:04:03,102 --> 00:04:06,980
Thank you for letting me
spend the night here, Abe.

120
00:04:07,064 --> 00:04:10,442
That house without Moishe…

121
00:04:10,526 --> 00:04:13,612
You can stay here as long as you want.

122
00:04:13,696 --> 00:04:19,159
<i>♪ Fabulous things ♪</i>

123
00:04:19,243 --> 00:04:24,873
<i>♪ With eyes that lull me to dreams… ♪</i>

124
00:04:24,957 --> 00:04:28,001
Just wanted to make sure it
was working in case they call.

125
00:04:28,085 --> 00:04:30,586
You're welcome to sit and watch with me.

126
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:34,882
-I could make us a drink.
-Ah, drink would be good.

127
00:04:34,966 --> 00:04:38,052
[SNIFFLING]

128
00:04:38,136 --> 00:04:41,512
You know, Moishe and I have
the most beautiful burial plots.

129
00:04:41,596 --> 00:04:42,015
Uh-huh.

130
00:04:42,099 --> 00:04:44,934
There's a tree right overhead,

131
00:04:45,018 --> 00:04:47,019
and Moishe sprung for a little bench

132
00:04:47,103 --> 00:04:50,356
-so people could sit.
-Sit? Sure, sure.

133
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,775
He also sprung for the
maintenance package,

134
00:04:52,859 --> 00:04:55,903
which means the cemetery
people have to cut the grass

135
00:04:55,987 --> 00:04:58,489
and empty the vases once a week.

136
00:05:00,116 --> 00:05:02,034
[BOTH EXHALE]

137
00:05:02,118 --> 00:05:03,911
Do you and Rose have your plots yet?

138
00:05:03,995 --> 00:05:05,788
Have you ever seen <i>The Twilight Zone?</i>

139
00:05:05,872 --> 00:05:07,665
It's a terrific program.

140
00:05:07,749 --> 00:05:09,792
No. Is it on now?

141
00:05:09,876 --> 00:05:12,920
No. No, it's not, damn it.

142
00:05:13,004 --> 00:05:14,964
You know, you and Rose
should really hurry up

143
00:05:15,048 --> 00:05:16,966
and get those plots.

144
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:19,802
You don't want to leave any
of the planning to the kids.

145
00:05:19,886 --> 00:05:21,929
[SCOFFS] Knowing Miriam,

146
00:05:22,013 --> 00:05:25,057
she'll probably want to
get you a funny casket.

147
00:05:25,141 --> 00:05:28,811
Like one that's shaped like
a shamrock or a <i>schvantz.</i>

148
00:05:28,895 --> 00:05:30,688
Can you imagine?

149
00:05:30,772 --> 00:05:32,648
Well, I can now.

150
00:05:33,649 --> 00:05:34,984
[SNIFFLES]

151
00:05:35,068 --> 00:05:37,820
Moishe wants an obituary
in the <i>New York Times,</i>

152
00:05:37,904 --> 00:05:39,989
just like Albert Einstein.

153
00:05:40,073 --> 00:05:42,533
He had the nicest obituary.

154
00:05:42,617 --> 00:05:44,952
I wonder who wrote it. [SNIFFLES]

155
00:05:45,036 --> 00:05:47,078
[SOBBING SOFTLY]

156
00:05:47,162 --> 00:05:49,789
We never… we never got to Turkey.

157
00:05:49,873 --> 00:05:51,791
Turkey? Why Turkey?

158
00:05:51,875 --> 00:05:55,211
We had a plumber that was from Turkey.

159
00:05:55,295 --> 00:05:57,589
[SHIRLEY SOBS, SNIFFLES]

160
00:05:59,257 --> 00:06:01,504
What are you gonna do if Rose goes first?

161
00:06:01,588 --> 00:06:01,968
What?

162
00:06:02,052 --> 00:06:05,555
Oh, no. I… I'm definitely going first.

163
00:06:05,639 --> 00:06:07,724
[SCOFFS]

164
00:06:07,808 --> 00:06:11,811
I think God is a cruel god. Don't you?

165
00:06:11,895 --> 00:06:14,731
Well, I actually think God is

166
00:06:14,815 --> 00:06:17,275
more of a brilliant marketing ploy.

167
00:06:18,318 --> 00:06:21,154
It's cruel that people
know they're going to die.

168
00:06:21,238 --> 00:06:23,239
It's like someone telling
you the end of a movie

169
00:06:23,323 --> 00:06:25,283
before you've seen it.

170
00:06:25,367 --> 00:06:28,161
I mean, how much fun is it
sitting through <i>Casablanca</i>

171
00:06:28,245 --> 00:06:31,456
if you already know Ingrid
Bergman isn't ending up

172
00:06:31,540 --> 00:06:33,833
with Humphrey Bogart?

173
00:06:33,917 --> 00:06:37,837
No tap dancing, no dwarves.

174
00:06:37,921 --> 00:06:40,715
One song, and Bogart walks off

175
00:06:40,799 --> 00:06:42,884
with the guy who hangs out with Nazis.

176
00:06:44,136 --> 00:06:46,847
It is a very overrated movie.

177
00:06:47,889 --> 00:06:50,058
You know, when my
grandfather was kidnapped…

178
00:06:50,142 --> 00:06:53,019
Hold on. Your grandfather was kidnapped?

179
00:06:53,103 --> 00:06:55,021
-Yes.
-By who?

180
00:06:55,105 --> 00:06:58,066
Well, first we thought it was anarchists,

181
00:06:58,150 --> 00:07:00,193
but then we found out it
was the Ubramawitz boys

182
00:07:00,277 --> 00:07:02,445
-from around the corner.
-Why?

183
00:07:02,529 --> 00:07:04,279
Oh, who knows why boys do anything?

184
00:07:04,363 --> 00:07:06,907
Anyhow, before we got him back,

185
00:07:06,991 --> 00:07:10,577
when my grandmother
thought he was gone for good,

186
00:07:10,661 --> 00:07:13,163
she said, "He's lucky.

187
00:07:13,247 --> 00:07:16,500
He died with all his teeth."

188
00:07:16,584 --> 00:07:19,336
That's the best you can hope for in life,

189
00:07:19,420 --> 00:07:22,631
that you die with all your teeth.

190
00:07:22,715 --> 00:07:24,925
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

191
00:07:27,011 --> 00:07:28,429
Abe.

192
00:07:29,847 --> 00:07:31,932
I just want you to know,

193
00:07:32,016 --> 00:07:36,520
if Rose goes first, I
will be there to help.

194
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,482
Thank you, Shirley.

195
00:07:40,566 --> 00:07:46,321
<i>♪ Somebody's walking in my dream ♪</i>

196
00:07:46,405 --> 00:07:47,823
[PHONE RINGS]

197
00:07:47,907 --> 00:07:49,950
-Susie Myerson and Associates.
-[FOOTSTEPS RUNNING]

198
00:07:50,034 --> 00:07:51,493
-Uh-huh.
-[LAUGHTER]

199
00:07:51,577 --> 00:07:52,953
Could you talk a little faster?

200
00:07:53,037 --> 00:07:55,539
We only have one line,
so while I'm talking to you,

201
00:07:55,623 --> 00:07:56,957
three other calls could
be trying to come in.

202
00:07:57,041 --> 00:07:58,834
SUSIE: Fucking working on it, Dinah!

203
00:07:58,918 --> 00:08:00,085
Wait.

204
00:08:00,169 --> 00:08:01,628
-Are the kids here?
-Yes.

205
00:08:01,712 --> 00:08:03,380
You have to warn me
when the kids are here

206
00:08:03,464 --> 00:08:04,965
-so I don't say "fuck."
-The kids are here.

207
00:08:05,049 --> 00:08:07,384
-Shit!
-I'll have her call you back.

208
00:08:07,468 --> 00:08:08,844
-Do I need to know who that was?
-[PHONE RINGS]

209
00:08:08,928 --> 00:08:10,929
Nope. Susie Myerson and Associates.

210
00:08:11,013 --> 00:08:12,931
-Pick a card.
-I am not picking a card.

211
00:08:13,015 --> 00:08:14,516
Fine.

212
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,518
I'll just look through
your wallet instead.

213
00:08:16,602 --> 00:08:18,645
Ah. She's got other boyfriends.

214
00:08:18,729 --> 00:08:20,271
You know that's not magic.

215
00:08:20,355 --> 00:08:22,106
That's five to ten where I come from.

216
00:08:22,190 --> 00:08:24,108
Not if you ask them to pick a card first.

217
00:08:24,192 --> 00:08:25,526
DINAH: …care of Dinah Rutledge.

218
00:08:25,610 --> 00:08:26,944
We brought some sfogliatelle today.

219
00:08:27,028 --> 00:08:28,529
-NICKY: I don't smell coffee.
-Bye.

220
00:08:28,613 --> 00:08:30,990
-Dinah, this I take personally.
-[PHONE RINGS]

221
00:08:31,074 --> 00:08:32,992
-Dinah…
-Make the coffee yourself, Nicky.

222
00:08:33,076 --> 00:08:34,869
Susie Myerson and Associates.

223
00:08:34,953 --> 00:08:36,245
-NICKY: Where are the coffee filters?
-Yes, we handle him.

224
00:08:36,329 --> 00:08:37,538
They're talking about me.

225
00:08:37,622 --> 00:08:38,831
You know I'm doing something here.

226
00:08:38,915 --> 00:08:39,874
I will have to check the calendar

227
00:08:39,958 --> 00:08:40,875
and talk to Miss Myerson about that.

228
00:08:40,959 --> 00:08:43,002
Look, I'll call you back.

229
00:08:43,086 --> 00:08:43,555
[RECEIVER CLICKS]

230
00:08:43,639 --> 00:08:45,296
[SIGHS] You know, you
should get a second line in here.

231
00:08:45,380 --> 00:08:46,547
SUSIE: Fuck you, Frank!

232
00:08:46,631 --> 00:08:47,965
-Wait, the kids are still here?
-[PHONE RINGS]

233
00:08:48,049 --> 00:08:49,550
-FRANK: Yep.
-Goddamn it.

234
00:08:49,634 --> 00:08:51,135
Susie Myerson and Associates.

235
00:08:51,219 --> 00:08:53,471
-MAGGIE: Dinah!
-Can you hold, please?

236
00:08:55,431 --> 00:08:56,891
What do you got, Maggie?

237
00:08:56,975 --> 00:08:59,310
Someone calling about
that weird magic guy.

238
00:08:59,394 --> 00:09:01,294
-Does he do birthday parties?
-Hold on.

239
00:09:02,105 --> 00:09:03,147
Hold on.

240
00:09:03,231 --> 00:09:04,315
Does Alfie do birthday parties?

241
00:09:04,399 --> 00:09:05,608
Only if it's Billy Wilder's.

242
00:09:05,692 --> 00:09:08,319
I love when they talk
about me like I'm not here.

243
00:09:08,403 --> 00:09:10,154
No, I really do.

244
00:09:10,238 --> 00:09:11,697
You know the minute they
get another chair in here,

245
00:09:11,781 --> 00:09:13,282
our relationship is over, right?

246
